President Biden has announced his nomination of Julie Su as Secretary of the Department of Labor. Su, who currently serves as the Deputy Secretary of Labor, has a strong background in fighting for workers' rights and has been instrumental in advancing President Biden's vision of an inclusive economy. Throughout her career, Su has held various positions in government, including as the Labor Secretary for the State of California, where she worked closely with unions and employers to create job opportunities for marginalized individuals. She has also been a prominent advocate for combating wage theft and protecting trafficked workers. Su's nomination is seen as a continuation of the administration's commitment to prioritize the well-being of workers and create accessible and stable job opportunities.